<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-2140] Cannot release Surefire on Windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-2140</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While trying to release Surefire on Windows today Git failed with: fatal: CRLF would be replaced by LF in pom.xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It turns out that the &lt;tt&gt;.gitattributes&lt;/tt&gt; is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# Auto detect text files and perform LF normalization
* text eol=lf

*.xml    text diff=xml
*.java   text diff=java
*.html   text diff=html
*.vm     text
*.fml    text
*.md     text
*.css    text
*.js     text
*.sql    text
*.png    binary
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know why LF is enforced, but most Git clients will perform &lt;tt&gt;autocrlf&lt;/tt&gt; and Maven Release Plugin will use platform line separator. Therefore, it will have CRLF after transformation and Git fails, thus release fails. I had to perform in Git Bash:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;git status | grep modified: | cut -c13-  | xargs -I^ dos2unix ^
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;through several stages to continue with the release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expectation: Either Git will be configured to use LS auto or Maven Release Plugin will force LF only.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
